							<img width="1536" height="1024" src="/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/ChatGPT-Image-May-27-2025-06_00_04-PM.png" alt="" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/ChatGPT-Image-May-27-2025-06_00_04-PM.png 1536w, /wp-content/uploads/2025/05/ChatGPT-Image-May-27-2025-06_00_04-PM-300x200.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px" />								</a>
		<p>One of our clients had over \$500,000 in home equity and no clear direction. Working alongside a Certified Financial Planner from our partner network, she was able to refinance a property, unlock \$200K in equity, and redeploy it into a mix of real estate syndications and Roth IRAs for tax-advantaged growth—all while keeping a safety net.</p><b>Are YOU in the same position?</b>
A CFP can make the difference between spinning your wheels… and climbing the next step on your Stairway. <a href="https://forms.stairwaymortgage.com/widget/survey/AepgdRkM7HMhrzkZ0AsO">Get a local introduction today.</a>		
					<h3>Where a Certified Financial Planner Adds the Most Value</h3>				
		<p>High-impact scenarios in debt, equity, or housing decisions that change plan outcomes.</p>		
									<h3>
							Structural Gaps &amp; Risk Misalignment						
					</h3>
									<p>
						Terms, amortization, points, reserves, or debt mix don’t match the IPS—CSA right-sizes structure to the plan and documents cash-flow/sequence-risk impact.					</p>
									<h3>
							Client in Transition						
					</h3>
									<p>
						Relocation, downsizing, divorce, inheritance, retirement—CSA unlocks/liquifies equity (HELOC, cash-out, bridge, HECM) while preserving liquidity and tax positioning.					</p>
									<h3>
							Build—or Distribute—Wealth						
					</h3>
									<p>
						For acquisitions or retirement income, CSA aligns cost of capital (DSCR/HELOC/recast) with cash flow, growth, and legacy objectives—coordinated with CPA/estate counsel.					</p>
					<h2>How a CFP Supports Your Financial Plan</h2>				
							<ul>
							<li>
										Convert home equity into plan-friendly liquidity without forcing asset sales.
									</li>
								<li>
										Evaluate refi vs. cash-out vs. HELOC/HECM/recast against tax and IPS constraints.
									</li>
								<li>
										Align real estate with portfolio (risk, duration, and cash-flow targets).
									</li>
								<li>
										Coordinate with CPA/estate attorney at term sheet and closing.
									</li>
								<li>
										Provide written impact memos: cash flow, reserves, breakeven, and risk notes.
									</li>
						</ul>
					<h2>When to Loop a CFP Into Your Advisor Team </h2>				
		<p style="text-align: center;">Moments when expert planning protects your cash flow, taxes, and long-term goals.</p>		
									<h3>
							Multiple properties or significant equity without a written debt policy.						
					</h3>
									<h3>
							Major life change: move, divorce, retirement, inheritance, liquidity need.						
					</h3>
									<h3>
							Idle equity / tight reserves where smart leverage improves resilience.						
					</h3>
									<h3>
							Concern about sequence-of-returns risk or variable income in retirement.						
					</h3>
									<h3>
							Desire to fund investments, gifting, or legacy without selling securities.						
					</h3>
